key "fama2001disappearing"

\end_inset

 is one of the most influential paper about dividends.
 Their idea is that the fraction of firms that pay out cash dividends has
 decreased substantially from 66.5% in 1978 to 20.8% in 1999.
 Some possible reasons could be structural shift in:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shift arises toward small firms with low profitability but strong asset
 growth (i.e., growth opportunity), characteristics typical for firms that
 never paid dividends
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
New lists from 3,638 in 1978 to 5,670 in 1997, with low profitability and
