\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Splitting sample into: former payers, payers, and never paid firms, they
 find some interesting stories.
 Former payers tend to be distressed with low earning and low investments.
 Never-paid firms tend to be more profitable than former payers and have
 strong growth opportunities.
 Dividend payers are, in turn, more profitable than never-paid firms but
 less investment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Next, they use logit regression to estimate 
