\begin_layout Standard
A seminal paper of Lintner (1956) propose that managers target a long-term
 payout ratio.
 They apply a Lintner dividend model:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Delta Dividend_{it}=\alpha_{i}+\lambda_{i}(\beta_{i}Profit_{it}-Dividend_{it-1})+\epsilon_{it}
\]

\end_inset


